{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013Z1fsnQHqMzBUQqtjyHLgN","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstepsCompleted: [1, 2]\n3\tlastStep: 2\n4\tstatus: complete\n5\tcompletedAt: '2026-03-17'\n6\tinputDocuments:\n7\t  - prd-overhaul.md\n8\t  - product-brief-codeharness-arch-overhaul-2026-03-17.md\n9\t  - ux-design-specification.md (v1, reworked)\n10\tworkflowType: 'ux-design'\n11\tnote: 'Full CLI UX spec — reworked for architecture overhaul with status visibility, failure detail, live mode'\n12\t---\n13\t\n14\t# CLI UX Specification — codeharness (v2)\n15\t\n16\t**Date:** 2026-03-17\n17\t**Revision:** Architecture overhaul — reworked for visibility, responsiveness, and clear failure reporting\n18\t\n19\t## Overview\n20\t\n21\tcodeharness is a CLI tool. No GUI, no web interface, no visual design. The UX is the developer experience in the terminal: command output, error messages, progress reporting, hook feedback, and proof document structure.\n22\t\n23\t**Core UX principle:** One screen, full picture. Progressive detail. Failures are specific and actionable.\n24\t\n25\t**Target user:** Developer who runs codeharness and checks back later. Needs to understand what happened in 10 seconds, drill into failures in 2 minutes, and never spelunk through log files.\n26\t\n27\t## Command Surface\n28\t\n29\t```\n30\tcodeharness <command> [options]\n31\t\n32\tCommands:\n33\t  init        Initialize harness in current project\n34\t  run         Start autonomous execution loop\n35\t  verify      Run verification pipeline for a story\n36\t  status      Show project state, run progress, and action items\n37\t  bridge      Import BMAD stories into beads\n38\t  onboard     Scan existing project and generate onboarding plan\n39\t  teardown    Remove harness artifacts (preserves project code)\n40\t  state       Read/write harness state flags\n41\t  retry       Manage story retry state\n42\t\n43\tOptions:\n44\t  --json      Machine-readable JSON output (all commands)\n45\t  --verbose   Verbose output for debugging\n46\t  --help      Show help\n47\t  --version   Show version\n48\t```\n49\t\n50\t### Command-Specific Options\n51\t\n52\t```\n53\tcodeharness init [--no-observability] [--no-frontend] [--no-database] [--no-api]\n54\t                 [--opensearch-url <url>]\n55\t                 [--otel-endpoint <url>]\n56\t                 [--logs-url <url>] [--metrics-url <url>] [--traces-url <url>]\n57\tcodeharness run  [--live] [--stop] [--max-iterations <n>] [--timeout <seconds>]\n58\tcodeharness verify --story <story-id>\n59\tcodeharness status [--story <id>] [--check-docker]\n60\tcodeharness bridge --epics <path> [--dry-run]\n61\tcodeharness onboard [scan|coverage|audit|epic] [--project-dir <path>]\n62\tcodeharness teardown [--keep-docker] [--keep-beads]\n63\tcodeharness state [get <key>|set <key> <value>|reset]\n64\tcodeharness retry [--status] [--reset] [--reset --story <id>] [--json]\n65\t```\n66\t\n67\t## Output Patterns\n68\t\n69\t### Status Prefixes\n70\t\n71\tEvery line of output uses a prefix:\n72\t\n73\t```\n74\t[OK]   Successfully completed action\n75\t[FAIL] Action failed — followed by actionable remedy\n76\t[WARN] Non-fatal issue — something to be aware of\n77\t[INFO] Informational — progress update or context\n78\t```\n79\t\n80\t### Symbols for Live/Status Views\n81\t\n82\t```\n83\t✓  completed successfully\n84\t✗  failed\n85\t◆  in progress\n86\t○  pending\n87\t✕  blocked/exhausted\n88\t```\n89\t\n90\t## Command UX: `codeharness status`\n91\t\n92\t### Default Output (One Screen)\n93\t\n94\t```\n95\tcodeharness v0.18.1 | nodejs | enforcement: front:OFF db:OFF api:OFF obs:ON\n96\t\n97\t── Project State ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n98\tSprint: 17/65 done (26%) | 5/16 epics complete\n99\tCurrent epic: Epic 3 — BMAD Integration (2/4 stories done)\n100\tModules: infra:OK verify:OK sprint:OK dev:OK review:OK\n101\t\n102\t── Active Run ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n103\tStatus: running (iteration 7, 2h14m elapsed)\n104\tCurrent: 3-3-bmad-parser-story-bridge → verifying (AC 4/7)\n105\tLast action: docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness bridge --dry-run\n106\tBudget: $23.40 spent | 47 stories remaining\n107\t\n108\t── This Run ───────────────────────────────────────────────────\n109\tCompleted:  4 stories (3-1, 3-2, 4-1, 4-2)\n110\tFailed:     1 story\n111\t  └ 2-3: AC 4 — status --check-docker exit 1 (attempt 3/10)\n112\tBlocked:    2 stories\n113\t  └ 0-1: retry-exhausted (10/10)\n114\t  └ 13-3: retry-exhausted (10/10)\n115\tSkipped:    3 stories (retry-exhausted)\n116\tIn progress: 1 story (3-3)\n117\t\n118\t── Action Items (this run) ────────────────────────────────────\n119\tNEW: 2-3 needs fix: status checks project-level containers, not shared\n120\tCARRIED: A56 status --check-docker wrong containers (3 sessions)\n121\t```\n122\t\n123\t### No Active Run\n124\t\n125\t```\n126\tcodeharness v0.18.1 | nodejs | enforcement: front:OFF db:OFF api:OFF obs:ON\n127\t\n128\t── Project State ──────────────────────────────────────────────\n129\tSprint: 17/65 done (26%) | 5/16 epics complete\n130\tLast run: 2h14m ago (4 completed, 1 failed, 2 blocked)\n131\tModules: infra:OK verify:OK sprint:OK dev:OK review:OK\n132\t\n133\t── Last Run Summary ───────────────────────────────────────────\n134\tDuration: 2h14m | Cost: $23.40 | Iterations: 7\n135\tCompleted:  4 stories (3-1, 3-2, 4-1, 4-2)\n136\tFailed:     1 story\n137\t  └ 2-3: AC 4 — status --check-docker exit 1 (attempt 3/10)\n138\tBlocked:    2 stories (retry-exhausted)\n139\tSkipped:    3 stories\n140\t\n141\t── Action Items ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n142\t[1] FIX 2-3: status checks project-level containers, not shared stack\n143\t[2] CARRIED A56: status --check-docker wrong containers (3 sessions)\n144\t\n145\t→ Run: codeharness status --story 2-3 for details\n146\t→ Run: codeharness run to resume\n147\t```\n148\t\n149\t### Story Drill-Down: `codeharness status --story <id>`\n150\t\n151\t```\n152\tStory: 2-3-observability-querying-agent-visibility-into-runtime\n153\tStatus: failed (attempt 3/10)\n154\tEpic: 2 — Observability Stack\n155\tLast attempt: 2026-03-18T03:42:15Z\n156\t\n157\t── AC Results ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\n158\tAC 1: [PASS] VictoriaLogs query returns structured logs\n159\tAC 2: [PASS] VictoriaMetrics query returns metrics\n160\tAC 3: [PASS] Agent queries logs during dev workflow\n161\tAC 4: [FAIL] Status command reports stack health correctly\n162\t  Command:  docker exec codeharness-verify codeharness status --check-docker\n163\t  Expected: exit 0 with \"running\" for all services\n164\t  Actual:   exit 1\n165\t  Output:   [FAIL] VictoriaMetrics stack: not running\n166\t  Reason:   Checks project-level container names (codeharness-victoria-logs-1)\n167\t            but shared stack uses (codeharness-shared-victoria-logs-1)\n168\t  Suggest:  Fix container name matching in src/commands/status.ts\n169\tAC 5: [PASS] Query endpoints accessible from verification container\n170\tAC 6: [ESCALATE] Observability data persists across sessions\n171\tAC 7: [PASS] OTLP instrumentation auto-configured\n172\t\n173\t── History ────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n174\tAttempt 1: verify failed (AC 4, same error)\n175\tAttempt 2: dev fix applied → verify failed (AC 4, same error)\n176\tAttempt 3: dev fix applied → verify failed (AC 4, same error)\n177\t\n178\tProof: verification/2-3-proof.md (5/7 pass, 1 fail, 1 escalate)\n179\t```\n180\t\n181\t## Command UX: `codeharness run`\n182\t\n183\t### Default (Background with Status File)\n184\t\n185\t```\n186\t$ codeharness run\n187\t[INFO] Starting autonomous execution — 6 ready, 1 in progress, 42 verifying\n188\t[INFO] Observability: shared stack running (VictoriaMetrics)\n189\t[INFO] Verification container: ready\n190\t\n191\tRunning in background. Check progress:\n192\t  → codeharness status          (one-screen summary)\n193\t 