{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TcDR4rWiBg4gxCauiyUHBy","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 14.1: WorkflowGraph Component\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n6\t\n7\t## Story\n8\t\n9\tAs a user,\n10\tI want to see a schematic workflow graph in the TUI,\n11\tso that I can see all tasks, their order, and loop blocks at a glance while a workflow is running.\n12\t\n13\t## Acceptance Criteria\n14\t\n15\t1. **Given** a running workflow with sequential flow steps `[\"create-story\", \"implement\", \"verify\"]`\n16\t   **When** the TUI renders\n17\t   **Then** the `WorkflowGraph` component displays each task as a node with its name, connected by `→` arrows in a single-line flow\n18\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n19\t\n20\t2. **Given** a workflow with a loop block `{ loop: [\"implement\", \"verify\"] }`\n21\t   **When** the TUI renders\n22\t   **Then** the loop block is rendered as `loop(N)[ implement → verify ]` where N is the current iteration count (starting at 0 before any iteration, incrementing each iteration)\n23\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n24\t\n25\t3. **Given** the `WorkflowGraph` component\n26\t   **When** it receives `flow`, `currentTask`, and `taskStates` as props\n27\t   **Then** each task node renders with a status indicator: pending tasks show dim text, the active task shows cyan text with a `◆` marker, completed tasks show green `✓`, and failed tasks show red `✗`\n28\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n29\t\n30\t4. **Given** a workflow is running\n31\t   **When** the Ink app renders\n32\t   **Then** the `WorkflowGraph` component is positioned between the `Header` and `StoryBreakdown` components in the layout\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** the `WorkflowGraph` component receives props\n36\t   **When** `flow` is an empty array or `taskStates` is empty\n37\t   **Then** the component returns `null` (renders nothing)\n38\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n39\t\n40\t6. **Given** the `RendererState` interface in `ink-components.tsx`\n41\t   **When** inspected\n42\t   **Then** it includes a `workflowFlow` field of type `FlowStep[]` (from `workflow-parser.ts`), a `currentTaskName` field of type `string | null`, and a `taskStates` field of type `Record<string, TaskNodeState>` where `TaskNodeState` is `'pending' | 'active' | 'done' | 'failed'`\n43\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n44\t\n45\t7. **Given** the `RendererHandle` interface in `ink-renderer.tsx`\n46\t   **When** inspected\n47\t   **Then** it includes an `updateWorkflowState(flow, currentTask, taskStates)` method that updates the workflow graph props and triggers a rerender\n48\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n49\t\n50\t8. **Given** `npm run build` is executed after all changes\n51\t   **When** the build completes\n52\t   **Then** it succeeds with zero TypeScript errors\n53\t   **And** `npm run test:unit` passes with no regressions in existing test suites\n54\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n55\t\n56\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n57\t\n58\t- [x] Task 1: Define `TaskNodeState` type and extend `RendererState` (AC: #6)\n59\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-components.tsx`, add `export type TaskNodeState = 'pending' | 'active' | 'done' | 'failed';`\n60\t  - [x] Import `FlowStep` from `./workflow-parser.js` in `ink-components.tsx`\n61\t  - [x] Add `workflowFlow: FlowStep[]`, `currentTaskName: string | null`, and `taskStates: Record<string, TaskNodeState>` to `RendererState`\n62\t\n63\t- [x] Task 2: Create `WorkflowGraph` Ink component (AC: #1, #2, #3, #5)\n64\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx` with the `WorkflowGraph` component\n65\t  - [x] Props: `{ flow: FlowStep[]; currentTask: string | null; taskStates: Record<string, TaskNodeState>; }`\n66\t  - [x] Return `null` if `flow.length === 0`\n67\t  - [x] For each `FlowStep` in `flow`:\n68\t    - If string: render as a task node with status indicator\n69\t    - If `LoopBlock`: render as `loop(N)[ task1 → task2 ]` with nested task nodes\n70\t  - [x] Status indicators via Ink `<Text>` color props:\n71\t    - `pending` → `dimColor` attribute\n72\t    - `active` → `color=\"cyan\"` with `◆` prefix\n73\t    - `done` → `color=\"green\"` with `✓` prefix\n74\t    - `failed` → `color=\"red\"` with `✗` prefix\n75\t  - [x] Connect nodes with ` → ` separator\n76\t  - [x] Wrap the entire graph in a `<Box flexDirection=\"column\">` with separator lines\n77\t\n78\t- [x] Task 3: Integrate `WorkflowGraph` into `App` layout (AC: #4)\n79\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-app.tsx`, import `WorkflowGraph` from `./ink-workflow.js`\n80\t  - [x] Import `LoopBlock` type from `./workflow-parser.js` (for type checking)\n81\t  - [x] Insert `<WorkflowGraph flow={state.workflowFlow} currentTask={state.currentTaskName} taskStates={state.taskStates} />` between `<Header>` and `<StoryBreakdown>`\n82\t\n83\t- [x] Task 4: Add `updateWorkflowState` to `RendererHandle` (AC: #7)\n84\t  - [x] In `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx`, import `TaskNodeState` from `./ink-components.js` and `FlowStep` from `./workflow-parser.js`\n85\t  - [x] Add `updateWorkflowState(flow: FlowStep[], currentTask: string | null, taskStates: Record<string, TaskNodeState>): void` to `RendererHandle` interface\n86\t  - [x] Implement: update `state.workflowFlow`, `state.currentTaskName`, `state.taskStates`, then call `rerender()`\n87\t  - [x] Add to `noopHandle` as empty function\n88\t  - [x] Initialize `workflowFlow: []`, `currentTaskName: null`, `taskStates: {}` in the initial `RendererState`\n89\t\n90\t- [x] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#8)\n91\t  - [x] Create `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx`:\n92\t    - Test: renders sequential flow as `task1 → task2 → task3`\n93\t    - Test: renders loop block as `loop(0)[ task1 → task2 ]`\n94\t    - Test: pending tasks render with dim text\n95\t    - Test: active task renders with cyan and `◆`\n96\t    - Test: completed task renders with green and `✓`\n97\t    - Test: failed task renders with red and `✗`\n98\t    - Test: returns null for empty flow\n99\t    - Test: returns null for empty taskStates\n100\t  - [x] Use `ink-testing-library` or Ink's `render()` test helper with snapshot or string matching\n101\t\n102\t- [x] Task 6: Verify build and tests (AC: #8)\n103\t  - [x] Run `npm run build` — zero TypeScript errors\n104\t  - [x] Run `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, no regressions\n105\t\n106\t## Dev Notes\n107\t\n108\t### Architecture Compliance\n109\t\n110\tThis story implements Epic 5, Story 5.1 (mapped to sprint Epic 14, Story 14-1) \"WorkflowGraph Component\" from `epics-multi-framework.md`. It covers:\n111\t- **FR24:** System can render a schematic workflow graph in the Ink TUI showing all tasks as nodes with directional flow\n112\t- **FR25:** System can highlight the currently executing task node in the workflow graph\n113\t- **FR28:** System can render loop blocks in the workflow graph with visual grouping and iteration counter\n114\t- **FR30:** System can show task completion status (checkmark, spinner, pending) per node in the workflow graph\n115\t\n116\tKey architecture decisions honored:\n117\t- **Decision 5 (TUI Workflow Graph Component):** New `WorkflowGraph` Ink component inserted between Header and StoryBreakdown. Renders a single-line flow with status indicators.\n118\t- **TUI Boundary:** TUI consumes workflow state updates. TUI does NOT dispatch drivers or write contracts. `WorkflowGraph` component receives flow structure and task states as props.\n119\t\n120\t### Rendering Format (from Architecture)\n121\t\n122\t```\n123\t━━━ Workflow: story 3-1 ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n124\t  implement ✓  →  verify ◆  →  loop(1)[ retry → verify ]\n125\t━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\n126\t```\n127\t\n128\tNote: Driver labels and cost/time per node are NOT part of this story. Those are covered in story 14-2 (Task Status & Driver Labels). This story focuses on the structural graph rendering and status indicators only.\n129\t\n130\t### Implementation Strategy\n131\t\n132\t1. **Types first:** Extend `RendererState` with workflow graph fields. Add `TaskNodeState` type.\n133\t2. **Component:** Create `ink-workflow.tsx` as a pure presentational component. It receives `flow`, `currentTask`, and `taskStates` as props and renders the graph. No side effects, no state management.\n134\t3. **Layout integration:** Insert the component into `ink-app.tsx` between Header and StoryBreakdown.\n135\t4. **Renderer handle:** Add `updateWorkflowState()` to the renderer handle so the workflow engine can push state updates.\n136\t5. **Tests:** Use Ink's test renderer to verify output strings and color attributes.\n137\t\n138\t### What Already Exists\n139\t\n140\t- `FlowStep` and `LoopBlock` types in `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` (lines 17-40) — reuse these directly\n141\t- `RendererState` interface in `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` (lines 53-62) — extend with workflow fields\n142\t- `RendererHandle` interface in `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` (lines 26-39) — add `updateWorkflowState()`\n143\t- `App` component in `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` — insert WorkflowGraph into layout\n144\t- `Header`, `Separator`, `StoryBreakdown` components in `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — existing layout components\n145\t- Status symbols: `✓` (done), `✗` (failed), `◆` (in-progress), `○` (pending) — already used in the codebase (see `ink-components.tsx` and UX spec)\n146\t- `noopHandle` in `ink-renderer.tsx` (lines 43-49) — add `updateWorkflowState` no-op\n147\t\n148\t### What NOT to Do\n149\t\n150\t- Do NOT add driver labels, cost, or elapsed time per node — that is story 14-2.\n151\t- Do NOT connect this to the workflow engine yet — this story builds the component and its API. The engine integration for calling `updateWorkflowState()` will come when the workflow engine is wired to the renderer.\n152\t- Do NOT use a spinner for active tasks. The architecture mentions \"cyan + spinner\" but spinners add complexity and dependency on `ink-spinner`. Use `◆` as the active indicator (consistent with existing `StoryBreakdown` component which uses `◆` for in-progress). Story 14-2 can upgrade to a spinner if needed.\n153\t- Do NOT use `async` or state hooks in the component — it is purely presentational, driven by props from the renderer handle.\n154\t- Do NOT add `ink-testing-library` as a new dependency if it's not already installed. Use Ink's built-in `render()` from `ink` for tests, or use `react-test-renderer` if already available.\n155\t\n156\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n157\t\n158\tFrom story 13-3 (Cross-Framework Workflow Execution):\n159\t- The workflow engine now writes output contracts after each task and passes them to the next task.\n160\t- `dispatchTaskWithResult()` returns `{ updatedState, output, contract }`.\n161\t- 4526+ tests passing across 168+ test files.\n162\t- The `workflow-engine.ts` already imports `FlowStep` and `LoopBlock` from `workflow-parser.js`.\n163\t- The engine iterates flow steps in `executeWorkflow()` — sequential steps and loop blocks are handled separately.\n164\t\n165\t### Git Intelligence\n166\t\n167\tRecent commits (94f08f9..c1dbd42) all follow the pattern of Epic 13 (output contracts). The last 3 stories (13-1, 13-2, 13-3) touched:\n168\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — heavily modified for contract integration\n169\t- `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-engine.test.ts` — extensive test additions\n170\t- `src/lib/agents/output-contract.ts` — new module\n171\t- `src/lib/agents/types.ts` — `OutputContract` interface added\n172\t\n173\tThis story does NOT touch `workflow-engine.ts` or `output-contract.ts`. It is isolated to the TUI layer.\n174\t\n175\t### Testing Patterns\n176\t\n177\tThe existing Ink component tests are in `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx`. Follow the same pattern:\n178\t- Import `render` from `ink-testing-library` (if available) or use Ink's `render()` + `lastFrame()`\n179\t- Create a minimal `RendererState` fixture and render `<WorkflowGraph>` directly\n180\t- Assert on output text content (task names, arrows, status symbols)\n181\t- Assert on color attributes (green for done, red for failed, cyan for active, dim for pending)\n182\t\n183\tCheck the test infrastructure before writing tests:\n184\t\n185\t```bash\n186\t# Check if ink-testing-library is available\n187\tgrep -r \"ink-testing-library\" package.json\n188\t# Check existing Ink test patterns\n189\thead -40 src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx\n190\t```\n191\t\n192\t### Project Structure Notes\n193\t\n194\tFiles to CREATE:\n195\t- `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx` — WorkflowGraph component (architecture specifies this exact path)\n196\t\n197\tFiles to MODIFY:\n198\t- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — Add `TaskNodeState` type, extend `RendererState` with workflow fields\n199\t- `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` — Import and insert `WorkflowGraph` into layout between Header and StoryBreakdown\n200\t- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` — Add `updateWorkflowState()` to `RendererHandle`, implement in controller, add to `noopHandle`, initialize state fields\n201\t\n202\tFiles NOT to modify:\n203\t- `src/lib/workflow-engine.ts` — Engine integration is NOT part of this story\n204\t- `src/lib/workflow-parser.ts` — Types already exist, no changes needed\n205\t- `src/lib/agents/*` — Driver/contract layer not touched\n206\t- `src/lib/ink-activity-components.tsx` — Activity display changes are story 14-3\n207\t\n208\t### References\n209\t\n210\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md#Story 5.1: WorkflowGraph Component]\n211\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Decision 5: TUI Workflow Graph Component]\n212\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — TUI Boundary]\n213\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-multi-framework.md — Project Structure (ink-workflow.tsx)]\n214\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-multi-framework.md — FR24, FR25, FR28, FR30]\n215\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-components.tsx — RendererState interface, existing layout components]\n216\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx — RendererHandle interface, noopHandle, controller pattern]\n217\t- [Source: src/lib/ink-app.tsx — App component layout]\n218\t- [Source: src/lib/workflow-parser.ts — FlowStep, LoopBlock, ResolvedTask types]\n219\t\n220\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n221\t## Verification Requirements\n222\t\n223\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/14-1-workflowgraph-component-proof.md)\n224\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n225\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n226\t\n227\t## Documentation Requirements\n228\t\n229\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n230\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/14-1-workflowgraph-component.md\n231\t\n232\t## Testing Requirements\n233\t\n234\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n235\t- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n236\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n237\t\n238\t## Dev Agent Record\n239\t\n240\t### Agent Model Used\n241\t\n242\tClaude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n243\t\n244\t### Debug Log References\n245\t\n246\t### Completion Notes List\n247\t\n248\t### File List\n249\t\n250\t- `src/lib/ink-workflow.tsx` — NEW: WorkflowGraph component\n251\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-workflow.test.tsx` — NEW: 9 unit tests for WorkflowGraph\n252\t- `src/lib/ink-components.tsx` — MODIFIED: Added `TaskNodeState` type, `FlowStep` import, extended `RendererState`\n253\t- `src/lib/ink-app.tsx` — MODIFIED: Imported and inserted `WorkflowGraph` between Header and StoryBreakdown\n254\t- `src/lib/ink-renderer.tsx` — MODIFIED: Added `updateWorkflowState()` to `RendererHandle`, implementation, noopHandle, initial state\n255\t- `src/lib/__tests__/ink-renderer.test.tsx` — MODIFIED: Updated `makeState` helper with n