{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015DPaRkLVcjS6SGn2GiQHXh","type":"tool_result","content":"3949\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-03 (Session 9, Part 3)\n3950\t\n3951\t**Timestamp:** 2026-04-03T14:45:00Z\n3952\t**Session window:** ~2026-04-03T09:20 to ~2026-04-03T11:15 (approx. 115 minutes)\n3953\t**Sprint progress:** 35/46 stories done (76%), Epics 1-13 complete\n3954\t\n3955\t---\n3956\t\n3957\t## 1. Session Summary\n3958\t\n3959\tThis session completed 6 stories across Epics 12 and 13, closing both epics. Story 13-3 was the capstone story for Epic 13 (Cross-Framework Workflow Execution), completing the entire multi-framework orchestration feature set.\n3960\t\n3961\t| Story | Phases Run | Outcome | Notes |\n3962\t|-------|-----------|---------|-------|\n3963\t| 12-2-opencode-driver-implementation | create, dev, review, verify | **Done** | OpenCode driver with fixture-based tests. 4478 tests pass. |\n3964\t| 12-3-driver-health-check-at-workflow-start | create, dev, review, verify | **Done** | Health check with timeout, timer leak caught by review. 4488 tests. |\n3965\t| 13-1-output-contract-schema-serialization | create, dev, review, verify | **Done** | Path traversal vulnerability caught by review. 4506 tests. |\n3966\t| 13-2-output-contract-prompt-injection | create, dev, review, verify | **Done** | Dead code wiring bug caught by review. |\n3967\t| 13-3-cross-framework-workflow-execution | create, dev, review, verify | **Done** | Capstone story — changedFiles dedup fix. 4545 tests. |\n3968\t| **Epic 12 & 13** | — | **Complete** | All 6 stories shipped, all ACs pass. |\n3969\t\n3970\t**Net output:** 6 stories completed and verified, 2 epics closed, +67 tests added (4478 → 4545), coverage held at 96.82%.\n3971\t\n3972\t---\n3973\t\n3974\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n3975\t\n3976\t### Bugs Found by Code Review (fixed in session)\n3977\t\n3978\t| Severity | Story | Issue |\n3979\t|----------|-------|-------|\n3980\t| HIGH | 12-3 | Timer leak — `setTimeout` never cleared on success path in `checkDriverHealth()` |\n3981\t| HIGH | 13-1 | Path traversal vulnerability — `taskName` with `../` could write outside `contractDir` |\n3982\t| HIGH | 13-1 | Empty input validation — empty `taskName`/`storyId` produced nonsensical filenames |\n3983\t| MEDIUM | 12-3 | Timeout error reported ALL drivers instead of only non-responding ones (AC #6 violation) |\n3984\t| MEDIUM | 12-3 | Double mock invocation in test |\n3985\t| MEDIUM | 13-1 | JSON parse error handling missing for corrupted contract files |\n3986\t| MEDIUM | 13-1 | Platform guard for `chmodSync` test (Windows) |\n3987\t| MEDIUM | 13-2 | `dispatchTask()` public API missing `previousOutputContract` parameter — dead code wiring |\n3988\t| MEDIUM | 13-2 | Missing integration test for workflow engine contract injection (AC #10) |\n3989\t| MEDIUM | 13-2 | Missing boundary test for output truncation at 2001 chars |\n3990\t| MEDIUM | 13-3 | `changedFiles` not deduplicated — same path could appear multiple times |\n3991\t| MEDIUM | 13-3 | Missing 3-step sequential flow test for AC #3 |\n3992\t\n3993\t**Summary:** 3 HIGH (2 security, 1 resource leak) and 9 MEDIUM issues caught and fixed. Code review continues to demonstrate high value — the path traversal vulnerability in 13-1 would have been a real security issue.\n3994\t\n3995\t### Known LOW Issues (deferred)\n3996\t\n3997\t- 12-2: Dead fixture files in test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/*.txt\n3998\t- 12-2: ~80 lines of classifyError/parseLine duplication across codex/opencode drivers\n3999\t- 12-2: `console.debug` for unparseable lines instead of structured logger\n4000\t- 13-1: No runtime schema validation at write time (by design)\n4001\t- 13-1: Concurrent write race condition (unlikely in sync code)\n4002\t- 13-2: No markdown sanitization in `formatContractAsPromptContext`\n4003\t- 13-2: `toFixed(2)` cost formatting shows `$0.00` for sub-cent costs\n4004\t- 13-3: `dispatchTask()` public API is effectively dead code internally\n4005\t- 13-3: Task 5 spec deviation — return type change not made for backward compat\n4006\t\n4007\t### Infrastructure / Process Issues\n4008\t\n4009\t- **AGENTS.md staleness (recurring):** Blocked `codeharness verify` in stories 12-2, 12-3, 13-1. This is the 5th+ session where AGENTS.md staleness causes verify failures. Still not auto-generated during dev phase.\n4010\t- **Proof format mismatches (recurring):** Verifier subagent generated wrong proof format in stories 12-3, 13-2, 13-3 (`### AC N:` vs `## AC N:`, `**Status:**` vs `**Verdict:**`, `**Verification tier:**` vs `**Tier:**`). Three separate format violations in one session.\n4011\t- **Pre-existing lint error:** `require-yield` at workflow-engine.test.ts persists across multiple stories.\n4012\t- **`codeharness stats --save` broken:** No `session-logs/` directory found. Stats cannot be generated from ralph logs.\n4013\t\n4014\t---\n4015\t\n4016\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n4017\t\n4018\t### Overall Cost (cumulative across all sessions)\n4019\t\n4020\t| Metric | Value |\n4021\t|--------|-------|\n4022\t| Total API-equivalent cost | $202.85 |\n4023\t| Total API calls | 1,568 |\n4024\t| Average cost per story | $3.46 (49 stories) |\n4025\t| Stories completed | 35/46 (76%) |\n4026\t\n4027\t### Cost by Token Type\n4028\t\n4029\t| Type | Tokens | Cost | % |\n4030\t|------|--------|------|---|\n4031\t| Cache reads | 83M | $124.55 | 61% |\n4032\t| Cache writes | 2.4M | $45.29 | 22% |\n4033\t| Output | 439K | $32.92 | 16% |\n4034\t| Input | 5.6K | $0.08 | <1% |\n4035\t\n4036\tCache reads dominate at 61% — expected behavior for multi-phase story execution where context accumulates.\n4037\t\n4038\t### Cost by Phase\n4039\t\n4040\t| Phase | Calls | Cost | % |\n4041\t|-------|-------|------|---|\n4042\t| verify | 749 | $89.96 | 44.3% |\n4043\t| orchestrator | 175 | $37.21 | 18.3% |\n4044\t| create-story | 207 | $23.29 | 11.5% |\n4045\t| dev-story | 182 | $20.26 | 10.0% |\n4046\t| code-review | 158 | $18.61 | 9.2% |\n4047\t| retro | 97 | $13.52 | 6.7% |\n4048\t\n4049\t**Verify is the most expensive phase at 44.3%.** This is consistent with prior sessions. The phase has the most API calls (749) and frequently retries due to format mismatches and AGENTS.md staleness.\n4050\t\n4051\t### Subagent Token Report Breakdown (This Session)\n4052\t\n4053\tAggregated from session issues log token reports for all 6 stories (15 subagent phases):\n4054\t\n4055\t| Phase | Total Tool Calls | Avg per Story | Top Tool |\n4056\t|-------|-----------------|---------------|----------|\n4057\t| create-story (5) | 89 | 17.8 | Read (34), Grep (26) |\n4058\t| dev-story (5) | 99 | 19.8 | Read (40), Edit (40) |\n4059\t| code-review (5) | 107 | 21.4 | Bash (38), Read (47) |\n4060\t| verify (5) | 70 | 14.0 | Bash (42), Read (15) |\n4061\t| **Total** | **365** | **24.3/story** | Read: 136, Bash: 91, Edit: 48 |\n4062\t\n4063\t**Key subagent-level observations:**\n4064\t\n4065\t1. **workflow-engine.test.ts read excessively:** Read 7-8 times per subagent in 13-3 (offset-based due to file size), and 3-4 times in 12-3 and 13-2. This single file accounts for ~20+ reads across the session. The file is too large for single reads.\n4066\t2. **Code review is the most tool-call-intensive phase** (21.4 avg), surpassing dev (19.8). Reviews run many Bash commands (builds, tests, lints) redundantly with dev.\n4067\t3. **No significant redundancy in create-story phases** — these were clean and efficient.\n4068\t4. **Verify phases had the fewest tool calls** (14.0 avg) but cost the most in aggregate due to retry loops from format mismatches.\n4069\t5. **`npm run build` run redundantly** in 12-3 dev phase (reported as redundant by subagent).\n4070\t6. **`npm run lint` and `ls verification/` each run twice** in 13-3 verify phase.\n4071\t\n4072\t### Estimated Session Cost\n4073\t\n4074\tWith 6 stories at ~$3.46 average, this session's estimated cost is **~$20-25** (including orchestrator and retro overhead).\n4075\t\n4076\t---\n4077\t\n4078\t## 4. What Went Well\n4079\t\n4080\t- **6 stories completed in ~115 minutes** — the fastest story throughput rate of any session (~19 min/story including all 4 phases).\n4081\t- **Two full epics closed** (12 and 13), bringing multi-framework orchestration to completion.\n4082\t- **Zero regressions** — test count monotonically increased from 4478 to 4545 with no test failures.\n4083\t- **Coverage held steady** at 96.79-96.82% across all stories, never dipping below the 80% floor on any file.\n4084\t- **Code review caught 3 HIGH severity issues** including 2 security vulnerabilities (path traversal, timer leak) and 1 correctness bug (AC violation). These are the kind of bugs that would cause real problems in production.\n4085\t- **Story scoping was excellent** — each story was well-bounded, no scope creep, no blocked dependencies.\n4086\t- **Pre-wiring from 13-2 paid off** — the `previousOutputContract` parameter was already wired into the dispatch API, making 13-3 implementation smooth.\n4087\t\n4088\t---\n4089\t\n4090\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n4091\t\n4092\t- **Proof format mismatches in 3 of 5 verify phases** — verifier subagents consistently produce proof documents in the wrong format. Three different format violations: header level (`###` vs `##`), verdict label (`Status` vs `Verdict`), and tier label (`Verification tier` vs `Tier`). This wastes retries and token budget.\n4093\t- **AGENTS.md staleness blocked verify in 3 stories** — same issue as previous 4+ sessions. The dev phase does not auto-generate AGENTS.md, so verify always fails first, fixes it, then re-verifies.\n4094\t- **`codeharness stats --save` still broken** — action item #59 from previous retro was not addressed. Cannot generate automated cost reports.\n4095\t- **Driver code duplication not addressed** — action item #41 (extract shared driver utilities) has been deferred for 5+ sessions. Now 3 drivers share ~80 identical lines each.\n4096\t- **Pre-existing lint error persists** — `require-yield` at workflow-engine.test.ts has been noted in 3+ sessions but never fixed.\n4097\t- **Dead fixture files created in 12-2** that tests don't use — minor waste.\n4098\t\n4099\t---\n4100\t\n4101\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n4102\t\n4103\t### Patterns to Repeat\n4104\t\n4105\t1. **Pre-wiring APIs in predecessor stories** (13-2 wired `previousOutputContract` for 13-3) — reduces capstone story complexity significantly.\n4106\t2. **Code review as security gate** — 2 path traversal vulnerabilities caught across stories 13-1 and 4-4. This pattern consistently finds real issues.\n4107\t3. **Small, focused stories** (~100-200 lines prod code) with clear AC lists enable fast, clean execution. All 6 stories this session followed this pattern.\n4108\t4. **Offset-based reads for large test files** — the subagents correctly adapted to workflow-engine.test.ts being too large for single reads.\n4109\t\n4110\t### Patterns to Avoid\n4111\t\n4112\t1. **Deferring AGENTS.md generation** — every session pays the cost in verify failures. Must be automated in the dev phase.\n4113\t2. **Hardcoded proof format assumptions** in verifier prompts — the format specification is clearly not reaching the verifier subagent consistently.\n4114\t3. **Accumulating LOW issues without a cleanup sprint** — 9+ deferred LOWs from this session alone. Technical debt is growing.\n4115\t4. **Running full test suites in code review** when dev already proved them passing — redundant `npm run build` and `npm test` calls.\n4116\t\n4117\t---\n4118\t\n4119\t## 7. Action Items\n4120\t\n4121\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n4122\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n4123\t| 64 | Fix proof format template — embed exact format spec with examples in verify skill prompt | HIGH | Tooling |\n4124\t| 65 | Auto-generate AGENTS.md during dev-story phase, not verify | HIGH | Process (carry-forward from #57) |\n4125\t| 66 | Fix `codeharness stats --save` to work without session-logs directory | MEDIUM | Tooling (carry-forward from #59) |\n4126\t| 67 | Fix pre-existing `require-yield` lint error in workflow-engine.test.ts | LOW | Cleanup (carry-forward from #60) |\n4127\t| 68 | Extract shared driver utilities (classifyError, parseLine) to common module | MEDIUM | Cleanup (carry-forward from #41, 5+ sessions) |\n4128\t| 69 | Split workflow-engine.test.ts into smaller focused test files | MEDIUM | Cleanup — reduces redundant reads |\n4129\t| 70 | Skip redundant `npm run build` in code-review when dev already passed | LOW | Process optimization |\n4130\t| 71 | Schedule a cleanup sprint to address accumulated LOW issues | MEDIUM | Planning |\n4131\t| 72 | Delete dead fixture files in test/fixtures/drivers/opencode/ | LOW | Cleanup |\n4132\t\n4133\t### Priority Recommendations for Next Session\n4134\t\n4135\t1. **Epic 14 (Dashboard & Visualization)** — next epic in backlog. Stories 14-1, 14-2, 14-3.\n4136\t2. **Fix AGENTS.md auto-generation (#65)** — highest-impact recurring issue. Saves ~$3-5/session in verify retries.\n4137\t3. **Fix proof format template (#64)** — second-highest recurring issue. 3 format violations this session alone.\n4138\t4. **Extract shared driver utilities (#68)** — 6 sessions deferred, now critical mass of duplication.\n4139\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BfFPFsnZZ17iSw4F7MUGEh","session_id":"1d40f54a-b143-44f0-8247-609f8fc4c105","uuid":"3d48743f-c625-41de-9b80-647a4bd0e4fb","timestamp":"2026-04-03T11:29:49.120Z"}
